This guide will help you update an Instance.

{% include 'alert/note', content: 'Currently, you can only update the name of an Instance. We will extend this tutorial with additional instructions once you can update other fields, too.' %}

## Requirements
To follow the steps in this tutorial, you should be able to log in to the Partner Portal, and have an Instance you created or have access to.

* [Accessing the Partner Portal](/get-started/accessing-partner-portal)
* [Setting Up a Site on Our Platform](/get-started/setting-up-site)

## Steps

Updating an Instance is a two-step process:

1. Locate Instance
2. Update Instance

### Step 1: Locate Instance

In the menu on the left, click on `Instances`, and select the Instance you would like to update. The information page of the Instance is displayed.

### Step 2: Update Instance

To update the Instance, click on `Edit`:

* `Name`: Edit the name of the Instance.

Click on `Update`. An `Instance was successfully updated.` message is displayed, and you can see that the information you edited has changed.

## Next steps
Congratulations! You have updated an Instance. Now you can learn about updating the configuration of an Instance:

